APPLE ARCADE
This section applies if you are playing a MobilityWare app that is part of Apple Arcade.
Data. MobilityWare does not collect, access, or store any of your data as part of the normal operation of our Apple Arcade games.
iCloud. Our Apple Arcade games provide full support for Apple’s iCloud service. This means they automatically save some of your game information (such as progress, daily challenges, and current game state) in a special way that allows the iCloud service to access it. If you have iCloud enabled on your device, the iCloud service will send that data into the cloud, on your behalf. It will also pull that data back down so that you can continue your experience on any of your devices. This process never involves MobilityWare servers or storage, in any way. You can enable/disable iCloud through your device settings.
Customer Support. We want you to have the best experience possible. If you choose to contact customer support from within our Apple Arcade games, we will populate an email with information that will help us solve your problem. This email will show all the information we are sending, in human-readable text. You will have full control over what, when, and how the information is sent. As this email is outside of the normal operation of our Apple Arcade games, any data sent to MobilityWare is covered by all of the terms of the MobilityWare Privacy Policy.
Anonymized Data. As part of the Apple Arcade service, MobilityWare may periodically receive data from Apple about the general usage of our games. This data is anonymized, which means it cannot be connected to individuals in any way.
Children. Apple allows children to play Apple Arcade games. Fortunately, MobilityWare does not collect, access, or store any of your data as part of the normal operation of our Apple Arcade games. As a guardian, you can provide additional protection by restricting access to iCloud, email, or websites on your devices. Please note that our customer support team and the MobilityWare websites are outside the normal operation of our Apple Arcade games – they should never be accessed by children or minors. Please see the “Use By Minors” section for more information.
